  description="Simple, transparent terms for using Meterly."
>
  <section>
    <h2>The platform</h2>
    <p>Meterly is a utility billing calculation tool for landlords and tenants splitting electricity bills, particularly for properties with solar panels.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Your responsibilities</h2>
    <p>You are responsible for the accuracy of the meter readings and rates you enter. Meterly acts as a transparent calculator. It is not a utility provider, payment gateway, or legal arbiter. Use the service in good faith.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>No advertisements</h2>
    <p>We don't show you ads. Utility billing software should be clean and focused.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>While we strive for mathematical accuracy, Meterly is provided "as is". We are not liable for financial disputes, damages, or discrepancies between you and your landlord or tenant. Verify your bills independently if in doubt.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>Questions about these terms? Email us at <a href="mailto:meterly.support@protonmail.com" class="email-link">meterly.support@protonmail.com</a></p>
  </section>
</LegalLayout>
